==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Griff
<hw>Griff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Gripe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Grasp; reach.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A vein of gold ore within one spade's <qex>griff</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. griffe, G. griff, prop., a grasping.]</ety>
<fld>(Weaving)</fld> <def>An arrangement of parallel bars for lifting
the hooked wires which raise the warp threads in a loom for weaving
figured goods.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Griff</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Griff
<hw>Griff</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person of mixed blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Griffe</ent>⟦br⟧
